how much he really loves me.</i>

900
01:06:07,051 --> 01:06:09,553
- He loves you plenty.
- More than Las Vegas?

901
01:06:09,720 --> 01:06:12,640
That's asking a lot.

902
01:06:12,723 --> 01:06:15,059
<i>(rings)</i>

903
01:06:15,309 --> 01:06:19,647
<i>(answer phone) Hi, this is Rita. I'm not in
right now. Please leave a message.</i>

904
01:06:19,814 --> 01:06:23,484
Rita, it's me, Ernie. I'm on my way home.
I hear you're seeing Thorn...

905
01:06:23,651 --> 01:06:28,739
...and I just don't want you to take it too
seriously. He's only with you to annoy me.

906
01:06:28,906 --> 01:06:33,160
I see. He couldn't possibly be interested
in me-that would be ridiculous.

907
01:06:33,327 --> 01:06:36,080
Rita, you're there.
This guy has terrible qualities.

908
01:06:36,247 --> 01:06:41,919
- For one thing, he's very manipulative.
- He seemed nice to me. Goodbye.

909
01:06:42,253 --> 01:06:45,006
Hello? Hello?

910
01:06:45,256 --> 01:06:47,925
Rita? Rita?

911
01:06:52,847 --> 01:06:55,516
Why do you smell the cork?

912
01:06:55,683 --> 01:06:58,352
Your eyes are hazel, aren't they?

913
01:06:58,436 --> 01:06:59,437
Green.

914
01:06:59,603 --> 01:07:01,605
<i>(Bilko) I never have sex on the first date.</i>

915
01:07:01,772 --> 01:07:07,445
Thank God, it's our third. Oh, this is such
a... Oh, can't you just smell that... salad?

916
01:07:07,528 --> 01:07:10,614
Yes, I have a reservation.

917
01:07:10,698 --> 01:07:16,203
Ah, this must be the table. You know,
what they do very well here is the garlic.

918
01:07:16,370 --> 01:07:18,706
Oh, I touched you.
My temperature is rising.

919
01:07:18,873 --> 01:07:24,462
<i>Waiter, could we have two glasses
of red house, uh... s'il vous please?</i>

920
01:07:24,628 --> 01:07:26,797
In.

921
01:07:27,131 --> 01:07:29,050
Bilko. What a fool.

922
01:07:29,216 --> 01:07:30,718
Yeah.

923
01:07:30,885 --> 01:07:33,804
How can he afford to eat here
on a sergeant's pay?

924
01:07:33,888 --> 01:07:38,059
- I'll be a lieutenant colonel very soon.
- No kidding?

925
01:07:38,225 --> 01:07:40,728
<i>(exaggerated laugh)</i>

926
01:07:40,895 --> 01:07:43,981
- That woman's kind of attractive too.
- You think so?

927
01:07:44,065 --> 01:07:46,734
Well, not compared to you, of course.

928
01:07:46,901 --> 01:07:49,737
Anyway, I understand
the oysters here are...

929
01:07:49,904 --> 01:07:53,407
...very, uh, very, uh... imported.

930
01:07:53,574 --> 01:07:56,494
- Just get me out of here fast.
- Relax, Paparelli.

931
01:07:56,661 --> 01:07:59,246
If you wanna make Rita jealous,
why not use Barbella?

932
01:07:59,413 --> 01:08:05,252
She knows Barbella. I needed someone
she can't recognise. Someone alluring.

933
01:08:05,503 --> 01:08:08,089
Thank you.

934
01:08:09,423 --> 01:08:14,512
Ah! Well, it's Rita Robbins
and Major Thorn! Ah! A-ha-ha, aha.

935
01:08:15,763 --> 01:08:19,016
Um, excuse me. One moment.

936
01:08:20,768 --> 01:08:26,107
<i>- (Bilko clears throat)
- She's coming over? She's coming over?</i>

937
01:08:27,108 --> 01:08:30,778
Ernie, you made Paparelli
get into drag just to make me jealous?

938
01:08:30,945 --> 01:08:36,450
Well, actually, he was already in drag.
Paparelli, scram! Get going.

939
01:08:54,552 --> 01:08:56,971
Rita, you can't marry Thorn.
You don't love him.

940
01:08:57,138 --> 01:09:00,558
Think of the children.
You're a Catholic and he's an asshole!

941
01:09:00,808 --> 01:09:06,230
How would you raise them? And he's
already cheating on you with Paparelli.

942
01:09:06,314 --> 01:09:09,233
Hi, soldier boy.

943
01:09:10,401 --> 01:09:13,738
<i>(hisses suggestively)</i>

944
01:09:15,906 --> 01:09:20,161
Sowicki never told you
I was marrying Thorn.

945
01:09:20,828 --> 01:09:25,249
You told Sowicki to call me.
You manipulated me. How could you?

946
01:09:25,416 --> 01:09:29,670
Why not? I have a master's in
manipulation from the University of Bilko.

947
01:09:29,837 --> 01:09:33,591
You tricked me. You sucked me in.

948
01:09:33,924 --> 01:09:37,511
This is the most turned on
I've ever been in my life.

949
01:09:37,678 --> 01:09:40,014
Rita, I'm so glad
we're back together again.

950
01:09:40,181 --> 01:09:43,017
Twelve more days.

951
01:09:50,441 --> 01:09:52,443
No wonder the hovertank never worked.

952
01:09:52,693 --> 01:09:57,782
Yes, sir. He's been diverting research
funds into his own private account.

953
01:09:57,948 --> 01:10:03,287
For all the differences I've had with Bilko
over the years, I've always liked him.

954
01:10:03,454 --> 01:10:05,706
The way he kept up the men's morale.

955
01:10:05,956 --> 01:10:10,044
The way he'd pretend to cry when I went
on leave. The way, on my birthday...

956
01:10:10,211 --> 01:10:15,716
...he'd have the men mow my name in
the main lawn with a big heart around it.

957
01:10:15,883 --> 01:10:19,387
- But now there'll be a court martial.
- Yes, sir.

958
01:10:19,553 --> 01:10:21,722
- Unless...
- Unless?

959
01:10:21,889 --> 01:10:25,726
It's just that I know we'd both
do anything to spare Bilko a court martial.

960
01:10:25,893 --> 01:10:28,479
If he could just be quietly punished.

961
01:10:28,562 --> 01:10:31,816
<i>(sighs) Yeah, sure.</i>

962
01:10:31,983 --> 01:10:34,151
But... but how?

963
01:10:34,402 --> 01:10:37,571
The CO has certain powers, sir.

964
01:10:37,655 --> 01:10:42,243
- Powers?
- Can't he, for instance, have a soldier...

965
01:10:44,245 --> 01:10:46,831
...trans...

966
01:10:47,581 --> 01:10:50,418
Trans... atlantic?

967
01:10:52,920 --> 01:10:55,840
Trans... vestite?

968
01:10:58,426 --> 01:11:01,929
- Transferred!
- What a wonderful idea.

969
01:11:02,096 --> 01:11:05,516
Yes, well, the wheels are always spinning.

970
01:11:05,683 --> 01:11:11,731
It'd have to be somewhere where there'd
be no chance of him making trouble again.

971
01:11:15,443 --> 01:11:17,987
Greenland?

972
01:11:18,112 --> 01:11:22,283
He's been out walking
by himself for, like, four hours.

973
01:11:22,450 --> 01:11:25,202
- What's he doin'?
- He's thinkin'.

974
01:11:25,286 --> 01:11:30,791
- I thought I heard him crying.
- He even asked for a box of tissues.

975
01:11:33,377 --> 01:11:35,046
<i>I guess you're happy.</i>

976
01:11:35,212 --> 01:11:38,549
Yeah. He hated the sarge.
He was probably helping Thorn to get him.

977
01:11:38,716 --> 01:11:41,218
- I was not!
- Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

978
01:11:41,469 --> 01:11:44,472
This is Bilko we're
talkin' about here. Bilko!

979
01:11:44,597 --> 01:11:46,724
Nobody gets the best of Bilko. Come on!

980
01:11:46,891 --> 01:11:49,644
<i>- That's right.
- (Paparelli) He'll think of somethin'.</i>

981
01:11:49,769 --> 01:11:53,314
Remember when I got the letter from
my wife sayin' she wanted to break up?

982
01:11:53,439 --> 01:11:56,150
- Remember what Bilko did?
- He got your wife back?

983
01:11:56,317 --> 01:11:58,736
No, he got me another wife. A better wife!

984
01:11:58,903 --> 01:12:02,907
- Yeah!
- He'll come up with his best plan ever.

985
01:12:03,074 --> 01:12:07,411
Listen, I pity Major Thorn.
When Bilko gets done with him...

986
01:12:07,536 --> 01:12:10,164
<i>- (Doberman) Sarge!
- Ten-hut!</i>

987
01:12:10,331 --> 01:12:12,208
Hey, Sarge!

988
01:12:12,333 --> 01:12:16,087
- Sarge!
- Sarge! You've come back!

989
01:12:16,504 --> 01:12:20,341
Ah, Doberman. The son I never wanted.

990
01:12:20,675 --> 01:12:23,928
Fall in and look this way!

991
01:12:27,515 --> 01:12:30,351
Hello, soldiers.

992
01:12:30,476 --> 01:12:34,105
<i>I'm talking to you.
Because that's what you are really.</i>

993
01:12:34,271 --> 01:12:37,274
Soldiers, every last one of you -
with a couple of exceptions.

994
01:12:37,441 --> 01:12:39,318
- He's got a plan.
- He sure does.

995
01:12:39,443 --> 01:12:43,280
I wanna tell you a little story.
There was once a little boy...

996
01:12:43,489 --> 01:12:47,159
...and that little boy had a dream to run
one of the most sophisticated...

997
01:12:47,451 --> 01:12:50,621
...illegal gaming operations
the US Army has ever seen.

998
01:12:50,788 --> 01:12:51,956
- He's not worried.
- Not a bit.

999
01:12:52,123 --> 01:12:54,458
And that little boy's dream came true.

1000
01:12:54,542 --> 01:12:58,129
But now they're trying to
snatch that dream back from him.

1001
01:12:58,295 --> 01:12:59,964
<i>- He is worried.
- That's not good.</i>

1002
01:13:00,172 --> 01:13:03,551
But what are the last two letters
in the name Bilko? K-O!

1003
01:13:03,718 --> 01:13:06,429
Of course, the first are B-l-L,
which is meaningless.

1004
01:13:06,637 --> 01:13:10,391
But still, am I giving up? No! Never!
Well, kind of, but not really...

1005
01:13:10,599 --> 01:13:14,270
...because there is no way
I am going to Greenland.

1006
01:13:14,395 --> 01:13:17,064
Well, you're probably wondering
if I have a plan.

1007
01:13:17,231 --> 01:13:21,569
Well, of course I have a plan!
A P-L-A-N. Plan.

1008
01:13:25,489 --> 01:13:27,825
But...

1009
01:13:28,326 --> 01:13:29,910
- He's got no plan.
- We're screwed.

1010
01:13:30,077 --> 01:13:34,081
- I have a plan, Sarge.
- But maybe a plan is not what I need!

1011
01:13:34,165 --> 01:13:37,418
What I really need is just a little puppy.

1012
01:13:37,585 --> 01:13:41,881
A little puppy with big, brown eyes
who'll just come to me and lick my face...

1013
01:13:42,089 --> 01:13:46,552
...and just love me so much,
no matter what kind of person I am.

1014
01:13:46,677 --> 01:13:47,762
<i>(Bilko sobs)</i>

1015
01:13:47,928 --> 01:13:50,723
Sarge, I really do have a plan.

1016
01:13:50,848 --> 01:13:55,436
<i>Oh, so now you have a plan.
Well, let's hear your plan, Wally.</i>

1017
01:13:55,686 --> 01:13:59,607
What if the hovertank did work? That'd
prove you haven't diverted the money.

1018
01:13:59,690 --> 01:14:02,360
Oh! That is so stup... What?

1019
01:14:02,526 --> 01:14:07,907
That would prove you hadn't been
diverting the money. Wouldn't it?

1020
01:14:09,575 --> 01:14:11,952
Are you saying you can get
the hovertank to work?

1021
01:14:12,119 --> 01:14:18,376
<i>No, of course not. But we don't need to
hold four aces if they think we hold'em.</i>

1022
01:14:20,461 --> 01:14:23,381
Permission to speak freely?

1023
01:14:23,589 --> 01:14:26,967
Tell me a bit more about this plan,
because I think that's actually...

1024
01:14:27,218 --> 01:14:29,845
If they come, deny everything.
Just act dumb.

1025
01:14:30,054 --> 01:14:34,141
Fender, I'm putting you in charge of that.

1026
01:14:35,893 --> 01:14:39,480
I love the nightlife, I like to boogie

1027
01:14:39,730 --> 01:14:41,732
I like to rock all night long

1028
01:14:41,857 --> 01:14:43,985
<i>(Bilko) Ahem.</i>

1029
01:14:44,151 --> 01:14:46,904
Oh... it's you, Bilko.

1030
01:14:47,071 --> 01:14:49,490
Sir, if I could talk with you
just for a moment.

1031
01:14:49,657 --> 01:14:53,160
If you've come to talk about Greenland,
you're wasting your time.

1032
01:14:53,327 --> 01:14:55,579
Frankly, Sergeant, I'm disappointed.

1033
01:14:55,746 --> 01:14:59,333
Sir, all I ever wanted was an honest
week's pay for an honest day's work.

1034
01:14:59,542 --> 01:15:03,337
- I didn't steal money, sir.
- Please, Bilko.

1035
01:15:03,504 --> 01:15:05,923
Let's just say goodbye.

1036
01:15:06,090 --> 01:15:08,092
And thank you.

1037
01:15:08,259 --> 01:15:11,429
- For what, sir?
- Well, for...

1038
01:15:11,554 --> 01:15:14,849
...always making me feel like
I actually ran this place.

1039
01:15:15,016 --> 01:15:17,601
Good old Fort Baxter.

1040
01:15:17,768 --> 01:15:20,438
I guess your garden
is one of the things you'll miss most.

1041
01:15:20,604 --> 01:15:22,356
Ah, yes. I love...

1042
01:15:22,523 --> 01:15:25,067
<i>- Miss? Why miss?
- The colonel hasn't heard?</i>

1043
01:15:25,151 --> 01:15:29,030
- In that case, it must not be true.
- What? Uh... they're closing Fort Baxter?

1044
01:15:29,280 --> 01:15:31,449
You didn't hear it from me.

1045
01:15:31,615 --> 01:15:34,702
Take good care of yourself in...
I've said enough.

1046
01:15:34,869 --> 01:15:37,038
Have you heard where they're sending me?

1047
01:15:37,204 --> 01:15:40,541
- You're stepping on your flowers.
- The hell with them! Where?

1048
01:15:40,750 --> 01:15:43,544
- Where are they sending me?
- It's just rumour, sir.

1049
01:15:43,711 --> 01:15:47,548
Oh, that fair skin
under the burning desert sun...

1050
01:15:47,715 --> 01:15:51,302
<i>Oh, my God. The desert sun.</i>

1051
01:15:51,677 --> 01:15:54,555
Remember, if you get lost, travel by night.

1052
01:15:54,805 --> 01:15:59,226
- How can they do this to me?
- The hovertank test was the last straw.

1053
01:15:59,393 --> 01:16:01,979
Too bad they didn't schedule it this week.

1054
01:16:02,146 --> 01:16:04,398
Well...

1055
01:16:04,565 --> 01:16:06,651
- Goodbye.
- Wha...? Wait!

1056
01:16:06,817 --> 01:16:10,529
- You mean the hovertank is working?
- Oh, I know what you're thinking, sir:

1057
01:16:10,738 --> 01:16:13,157
..."Arrange a public demonstration ASAP."

1058
01:16:13,324 --> 01:16:15,826
"Call the Pentagon
and the Department of the Army."

1059
01:16:15,993 --> 01:16:18,829
- All right.
- I've already taken that liberty, sir.

1060
01:16:18,913 --> 01:16:20,915
- Thank you.
- Oh, that picture of you...

1061
01:16:20,998 --> 01:16:23,501
...standing triumphant at the test.

1062
01:16:23,751 --> 01:16:28,422
That'll keep me warm
on those lonely nights in Greenland.

1063
01:16:28,589 --> 01:16:31,008
<i>In Greenland, sir.</i>

1064
01:16:31,175 --> 01:16:33,177
Oh. Yes.

1065
01:16:33,427 --> 01:16:36,013
Well, goodbye.

1066
01:16:37,056 --> 01:16:40,226
- Ah, Bi...
- Yes, sir?

1067
01:16:41,352 --> 01:16:44,605
If the test goes well,
you won't be transferred.

1068
01:16:44,772 --> 01:16:47,858
Well, thank you, sir! I'm stunned!

1069
01:16:47,984 --> 01:16:50,277
Just as a formality,
I've put that in writing.

1070
01:16:50,444 --> 01:16:55,199
If you could just sign here
and here, and initial here.

1071
01:16:57,535 --> 01:17:00,204
- Here?
- Uh, no. Here.

1072
01:17:00,371 --> 01:17:03,082
And I'll just notarise that.

1073
01:17:03,124 --> 01:17:08,129
- And I'll waive the usual ten-dollar fee.
- Oh. Thank you.

1074
01:17:08,337 --> 01:17:11,465
Here you are. Good day.

1075
01:17:12,466 --> 01:17:14,468
No, it'll hover. But as before...

1076
01:17:14,593 --> 01:17:18,889
...it will go completely haywire
if we attempt to fire the cannon.

1077
01:17:19,056 --> 01:17:21,434
We know that. We just need
a couple of hours with it.

1078
01:17:21,642 --> 01:17:25,604
- Let's get started.
- It's a $70-million piece of equipment.

1079
01:17:25,813 --> 01:17:29,066
You think I'm gonna allow
one of your men to fool around with it?

1080
01:17:29,191 --> 01:17:31,652
- I think not.
- Oh. Mm-hm.

1081
01:17:31,777 --> 01:17:35,740
Oh, boy. Oh, my, is it hot in here or what?

1082
01:17:35,906 --> 01:17:38,909
What's this? Oh!
I almost forgot I had these.

1083
01:17:39,118 --> 01:17:41,579
It's the IOUs from the poker game.

1084
01:17:41,704 --> 01:17:46,500
- Would he like to use my tools?
- That would be nice.

1085
01:17:49,837 --> 01:17:53,424
- You saw it?
- Yeah, it blew up the ammunition shed.

1086
01:17:53,591 --> 01:17:56,802
<i>- A perfect hit.
- (louder) The hovertank?</i>

1087
01:17:56,886 --> 01:17:59,680
- I thought that thing was busted.
- Yeah, it was.

1088
01:17:59,930 --> 01:18:01,682
But the kid, Wally, he fixed it.

1089
01:18:01,849 --> 01:18:04,685
He said the key was the...

1090
01:18:04,852 --> 01:18:07,229
The...?

1091
01:18:07,772 --> 01:18:11,275
The fire-control
and super-elevator board.

1092
01:18:11,442 --> 01:18:15,363
- Imagine that.
- Yeah, the super-elevator board.

1093
01:18:15,571 --> 01:18:20,618
And the great thing is, if it works
at the demonstration, Bilko gets to stay.

1094
01:18:20,826 --> 01:18:23,037
Great!

1095
01:18:50,982 --> 01:18:53,192
Yeah.

1096
01:19:14,463 --> 01:19:19,010
- Wonderful to see you again, General.
- You, too, Colonel. Mrs Hall.

1097
01:19:19,176 --> 01:19:23,597
- And, of course, you know Major Thorn.
- Thorn.

1098
01:19:34,942 --> 01:19:37,695
<i>(deep sigh)</i>

1099
01:19:44,744 --> 01:19:48,039
- Tank crew ready, sir.
- Very good, Bilko. General.

1100
01:19:48,205 --> 01:19:50,624
Master Sergeant Bilko.
It's an honour to meet you.

1101
01:19:50,791 --> 01:19:54,462
- You look terrific! Have you lost weight?
- Who is this?

1102
01:19:54,628 --> 01:19:59,216
Members of Congress, General Tennyson,
colleagues from the defence industries...

1103
01:19:59,383 --> 01:20:03,012
...distinguished guests, welcome.

1104
01:20:03,387 --> 01:20:05,806
The weapon system
you are about to see today...

1105
01:20:05,973 --> 01:20:11,562
...can be called the world's first
truly all-terrain assault vehicle...

1106
01:20:11,979 --> 01:20:17,485
...which I'm proud to say was developed
entirely in-house, here at Fort Baxter.

1107
01:20:17,652 --> 01:20:22,156
I give you the armoured attack platform
to lead American defence forces...

1108
01:20:22,281 --> 01:20:26,661
...into the 21st century.
The HTX-1 hovertank.

1109
01:20:38,089 --> 01:20:42,259
Water and rough terrain can stop
an ordinary M1 or APC...

1110
01:20:42,426 --> 01:20:45,805
...but the hovertank can literally rise
above these obstacles.

1111
01:20:46,013 --> 01:20:49,892
And that is the capability
we will show you here today.

1112
01:20:49,976 --> 01:20:53,562
Hovertank, you are looking good.

1113
01:20:54,271 --> 01:20:58,025
Hovertank, fire when ready. Hoo-ah!

1114
01:20:58,442 --> 01:21:01,112
<i>(groans)</i>

1115
01:21:14,041 --> 01:21:16,794
<i>(applause)</i>

1116
01:21:25,136 --> 01:21:29,223
Ha. This little bird packs a deadly punch.

1117
01:21:59,086 --> 01:22:01,881
Fire in the hole!

1118
01:22:35,247 --> 01:22:41,212
- You hit the wrong button, Rastahead!
- It's not my fault! He wired it wrong!

1119
01:22:42,880 --> 01:22:45,549
Any questions?

1120
01:23:07,029 --> 01:23:09,907
